      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC12765497",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_1",
      "text": "With the rising incidence of cancer-related mortality, new enabling technologies are necessary to offer comprehensive molecular profiles of patients in order to assist clinicians to establish an early presumptive diagnosis.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC12765497:abstract:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC12765497",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_2",
      "text": "Biosensors that are technically comparable to conventional laboratory diagnostics have been developed.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC12765497:abstract:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC12765497",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_3",
      "text": "Hence, smartphone-assisted biosensors have been developed for point-of-care utilization. They are faster, simpler, and more affordable than standard examinations and first-generation biosensors.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC12765497:abstract:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC12765497",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_4",
      "text": "Therefore, this review focuses primarily on cutting edge developments in smartphone-assisted biosensing platforms that are most relevant to early cancer diagnosis, including optical and electrochemical biosensors, and cancer imaging.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
